dct_description_sm: Geological Survey of New Jersey. Atlas Sheet 35 (1907) New Jersey Geological Survey Relief show by 10 and 5 ft. contour interval and spot heights. Depth shown by contour ans soundiings in feet at low tide.Title was not given. Region covered: vicinity of Millville. Original survey 1886, principal culture revised 1907. The shore line of tidal waters, and the triangulation are in part from the U.S. Coast and Geodetic Survey. The highways, railroads and some other details were revisde between 1905 and 1907, the forests are as in 1886.
dct_publisher_sm: Trenton, N.J. : Geological Survey of New Jersey, 1907.
